lastVersion.statementHTML:
Goal

Ethan loves eating. He'll eat either food A, food B, or both. His initial satisfactory value t is 0.

Every time he eats food A or B, he gains a satisfactory value of a and b, respectively. That is, he adds a or b onto t.

Ethan has to eat ca amount of food of type A and cb amount of food of type B to reach a satisfactory value of exactly T. Help him find ca and cb, or determine if it's impossible.
Input
A line consisting of three space-separated unsigned integers a, b and T, representing the satisfactory value of a and b and the target satisfactory value, respectively.
Output
The first line is either YES or NO, determining whether or not Ethan can reach a satisfactory value of T.

If the output is YES, you must output in the second line, two space-separated unsigned integers ca and cb, representing the number of foods of type A and B Ethan has to eat, respectively.

If there are multiple options, output the one with the largest ca.
Constraints
1 <= a, b <= 1000
1 <= T <= 10000
Example
Input
3 5 11
Output
YES
2 1
